cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a neural network framework for face recognition, which involves image processing and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video-based face recognition, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
